| Type | Full Form                    | Purpose                                     | Common Commands                                      |
| ---- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| DDL  | Data Definition Language     | Used to define or modify database structure | `CREATE`, `ALTER`, `DROP`, `TRUNCATE`, `RENAME`      |
| DML  | Data Manipulation Language   | Used to insert, update, and delete data     | `INSERT`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`                         |
| DQL  | Data Query Language          | Used to fetch/query data                    | `SELECT`                                             |
| DCL  | Data Control Language        | Used to control user permissions and access | `GRANT`, `REVOKE`                                    |
| TCL  | Transaction Control Language | Used to manage transactions in database     | `COMMIT`, `ROLLBACK`, `SAVEPOINT`, `SET TRANSACTION` |


==============

Detailed Explanation Table

| Type | Works On         | Auto Commit | Example                              |
| ---- | ---------------- | ----------- | ------------------------------------ |
| DDL  | Table structure  | Yes         | `CREATE TABLE students (...);`       |
| DML  | Table data       | No          | `INSERT INTO students VALUES (...);` |
| DQL  | Fetch data       | No          | `SELECT * FROM students;`            |
| DCL  | User permissions | Yes         | `GRANT SELECT ON students TO user1;` |
| TCL  | Transactions     | No          | `COMMIT;`                            |


