SQL Commands with Before & After Table Examples
1. DDL (Data Definition Language)
Purpose

Used to create or modify table structure.

Commands

CREATE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE, RENAME

Example: CREATE TABLE
Before

Database has no table named students.

Query
CREATE TABLE students (
    student_id INT,
    name VARCHAR(50)
);
After
students table
student_id	name
Empty	Empty

(Table structure created)

2. DML (Data Manipulation Language)
Purpose

Used to insert, update, and delete data.

Commands

INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE

INSERT Example
Before
student_id	name
Empty	Empty
Query
INSERT INTO students
VALUES (1, 'Arun');
After
student_id	name
1	Arun
UPDATE Example
Before
student_id	name
1	Arun
Query
UPDATE students
SET name = 'Ravi'
WHERE student_id = 1;
After
student_id	name
1	Ravi
DELETE Example
Before
student_id	name
1	Ravi
Query
DELETE FROM students
WHERE student_id = 1;
After
student_id	name
Empty	Empty
3. DQL (Data Query Language)
Purpose

Used to fetch data.

Command

SELECT

Before
student_id	name
1	Arun
2	Priya
Query
SELECT * FROM students;
Result
student_id	name
1	Arun
2	Priya

(No changes in table)

4. DCL (Data Control Language)
Purpose

Used to control access permissions.

Commands

GRANT, REVOKE

GRANT Example
Before

User student1 has no permission.

Query
GRANT SELECT
ON students
TO 'student1'@'localhost';
After
User	Permission
student1	SELECT
REVOKE Example
Before
User	Permission
student1	SELECT
Query
REVOKE SELECT
ON students
FROM 'student1'@'localhost';
After
User	Permission
student1	No Permission
5. TCL (Transaction Control Language)
Purpose

Used to manage transactions.

Commands

COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT

COMMIT Example
Before
student_id	name
1	Arun
Query
INSERT INTO students
VALUES (2, 'Kiran');

COMMIT;
After
student_id	name
1	Arun
2	Kiran

(Data permanently saved)

ROLLBACK Example
Before
student_id	name
1	Arun
Query
INSERT INTO students
VALUES (2, 'Kiran');

ROLLBACK;
After
student_id	name
1	Arun

(Kiran row removed because transaction cancelled)

